    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-09-07T06:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-09-07T06:00:00-05:00" n="479"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d479">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">320.2 AA/9–751: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Lebanon</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_BJH1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bruins</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Department of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d479fn1">Repeated for information to Tel Aviv, Damascus,
                        Amman, Cairo, Baghdad, Jidda, London, and Paris.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Beirut</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-09-07T13:00:00+02:00"
                            >September 7, 1951—1 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>229. <gloss target="#t_Rapun1">Rapun</gloss> 214. 1. <persName corresp="#p_BJB2"
                        >Blandford</persName> saw <persName corresp="#p_SHM1">Sharett</persName> and
                        <persName corresp="#p_MG3">Meron</persName> Jerusalem 6th. Re refugees still
                    receiving <gloss target="#t_PRA1">PRA</gloss> rations in Israel <persName
                        corresp="#p_BJB2">Blandford</persName> took offensive stating that three
                    years had now passed and Israel had not yet succeeded reintegrating over 20,000
                    Israeli citizens of which 3,000 Jews. When <persName corresp="#p_MG3"
                        >Meron</persName> brought up previous Israeli requests for <gloss
                        target="#t_PRA1">PRA</gloss> reintegration assistance <persName
                        corresp="#p_BJB2">Blandford</persName> replied Israel who is asking and
                    getting large-scale aid from abroad to reintegrate newcomers should attack this
                    “unfinished business” first and reintegrate own refugees without calling on
                        <gloss target="#t_UN1">UN</gloss>. <persName corresp="#p_BJB2"
                        >Blandford</persName> stressed more beneficial to Israel that <gloss
                        target="#t_PRA1">PRA</gloss> funds be devoted exclusively to resettlement
                    refugees Arab States. <gloss target="#t_FonMin1">FonMin</gloss>
                    <persName corresp="#p_MG3">Meron</persName> seemed most impressed these
                    arguments and promised definite Israeli reply within fortnight.</p>
                <pb facs="0893" n="853" xml:id="pg_853"/>
                <p>2. In passing <persName corresp="#p_SHM1">Sharett</persName> stated Israel now
                    prepared discuss compensation without insisting general settlement. Also made
                    several unclear statements re compensation negots gist of which seemed to be
                    that if Israelis and Arabs met face to face Israel would raise question war
                    damage for tactical bargaining purposes. However if negots held through <gloss
                        target="#t_UN1">UN</gloss> machinery Israel prepared forego war damage
                    claims. Perhaps Emb Tel Aviv can clarify.<note n="2" xml:id="d479fn2">See
                        telegram 229 from Tel Aviv, September 11, <ref target="#pg_854">p.
                        854</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_BJH1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Bruins</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
